com.bigdata.striterator

Class GenericStriterator<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bigdata.striterator.Striterator<Iterator<E>,E>
      • com.bigdata.striterator.GenericStriterator<E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IStriterator<Iterator<E>,E>, ICloseable, ICloseableIterator<E>, Enumeration<E>, Iterator<E>

    public class GenericStriterator<E>
extends Striterator<Iterator<E>,E>
    Streaming iterator class that suppresses generic types. Striterator patterns are often used to convert the type of the elements visited by the underlying iterator. That and the covarying generics combine to make code using generics and striterators rather ugly.
